news.title: China's top real estate regulator vows to tackle property delivery risks: Xinhua
news.para: Wang Menghui, head of the Ministry of Housing and Urban-Rural Development, also told Xinhua that China will keep its real estate policies consistent and stable, while strengthening coordination in areas including finance, and land and market supervision.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh CM lays foundation stones of Indore metro
news.para: The foundation stone for the first phase of the 31.55-kilometre-long Indore's metro rail project, estimated to cost Rs 7,500.80 crore, was laid by then CM Kamal Nath on September 14, 2019.

news.title: Chennai: Metro in suburbs on fast-track
news.para: “We have set a 2025 deadline for Power House to Poonamallee stretch (corridor 4). In a few months, other elevated stretches will also be ready. We are pushing for the deadline, but it depends on the contractor,” an official said.

news.title: China's central bank says to promote healthy development of property market
news.para: The statement from the People's Bank of China (PBOC), made following its fourth-quarter monetary policy committee meeting, is the latest sign that Chinese regulators are marginally easing curbs on the property sector to prevent a hard-landing.

news.title: WeWork India revenue up 33% at Rs 800 crore in 2021
news.para: Looking at the growing demand for flexibility, Karan Virwani, CEO, WeWork India said the company would expand its portfolio by one million square feet area with capacity of about 20,000 desks.

news.title: Jaipur development body to fix use of greenfield airport land
news.para: After the decision was taken that airport will not be constructed on the reserved land, the town planning wing has started the exercise to earmark the area as ‘special area’ in the Master Plan 2025. The notification for the same will be released soon.

news.title: Mumbai: Producer remanded to judicial custody in Rs 13.7 crore housing fraud
news.para: Jain was arrested by the Economic Offences Wing (EOW) in 2016 for allegedly cheating home buyers; later, multiple FIRs were registered against him and his company.

news.title: Mumbai: Tenants, landlords unite to redevelop Kamathipura
news.para: For the 800 landlords and over 8,000 tenants of Kamathipura, who have waited years for their properties to be redeveloped, hope is finally on the horizon.

news.title: Chennai development body says no to real estate on water bodies
news.para: It includes a 20.6 acre land parcel, which is the surplus course of Kosasthalaiyar River at Vallur in the northern suburbs belonging to a temple in neighbouring Andhra Pradesh, which was being considered for a residential layout.

news.title: Rajasthan: 2.49 lakh PMAY-Gramin beneficiaries yet to get first instalment
news.para: It has been directed to the districts by rural development secretary K K Pathak to complete payment of first instalment by December 31.

news.title: Greater Noida: 1,450 apply for 83 industrial plots on offer
news.para: Officials said there were 1,450 applications for the plots, which ranged from 450 to 2,000sqm. More than 1,350 of these applicants opted for a one-time payment, the officials said.

news.title: Gurugram and Faridabad will be connected by metro soon: Haryana CM
news.para: A formal statement in this regard was made by the Haryana chief minister Manohar Lal Khattar before the state assembly during the winter session on Wednesday.

news.title: Additional collectors to be accountable for illegal buildings: Telangana government
news.para: The district collector has recommended action against the municipal commissioners and gram panchayat secretaries who worked earlier, for failing to stop the illegal structures including some on the lake’s buffer zone.

news.title: Punish officers allowing illegal buildings: Karnataka HC
news.para: It has said that jurisdictional engineers have to immediately take suo motu action or act on the basis of complaints against such constructions and added that departmental probe should be initiated against officers showing lackadaisical attitude in performing their duty to check the growth of such illegal constructions in their jurisdiction.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body approves waiver of penalty for property dues
news.para: According to the GB agenda, the property tax defaulters will get a 90% waiver on the delay charges levied on the penalty, if they pay the outstanding dues by January 2022.
